ming-creek\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Implement the following plan:\\n\\n# Plan: Remove Strategy Abstraction & Add `commit_linking` Setting\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nThe CLI has a `Strategy` interface abstraction (`strategy.go`) designed to support multiple session strategies, but only one implementation (`ManualCommitStrategy`) has ever existed. The current behavior prompts users on every commit to link/unlink the session. Per RFD-003 decisions, we need to:\\n\\n1. Remove the `Strategy` interface (inline the single implementation)\\n2. Add a `commit_linking` setting (`always` / `prompt`)\\n3. Default new users to `always` (auto-link), existing users to `prompt` (preserve current behavior)\\n4. No user migration action required\\n\\n## Implementation Steps\\n\\n### Step 1: Add `commit_linking` setting to `EntireSettings`\\n\\n**Files:**\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/settings/settings.go`\\n\\n**Changes:**\\n- Add `CommitLinking string` field to `EntireSettings` struct with `json:\\\"commit_linking,omitempty\\\"`\\n- Add `GetCommitLinking() string` resolver method:\\n  - If `CommitLinking` is explicitly set → return it\\n  - Otherwise → return `\\\"prompt\\\"` (safe default, preserves existing user behavior)\\n- Add validation constant `CommitLinkingAlways = \\\"always\\\"`, `CommitLinkingPrompt = \\\"prompt\\\"`\\n- Update `mergeJSON()` to handle the `commit_linking` field override\\n\\n### Step 2: Set `commit_linking: \\\"always\\\"` for new installations\\n\\n**Files:**\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/setup.go`\\n\\n**Changes:**\\n- In the `entire enable` setup flow, set `settings.CommitLinking = \\\"always\\\"` before writing settings\\n- This means new users get auto-linking by default\\n- Existing users who don't have the field keep getting `\\\"prompt\\\"` via the `GetCommitLinking()` default\\n\\n### Step 3: Modify `PrepareCommitMsg` to respect `commit_linking`\\n\\n**Files:**\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go`\\n\\n**Changes:**\\n- Load settings via `settings.Load(ctx)` at the start of `PrepareCommitMsg`\\n- Call `settings.GetCommitLinking()` to determine mode\\n- When `\\\"always\\\"`:\\n  - For `source=\\\"message\\\"` (-m flag): skip `askConfirmTTY()`, just add the trailer directly\\n  - For `source=\\\"\\\"` or `\\\"template\\\"` (editor flow): add trailer with comment (user can still remove it) — same as current behavior for this case\\n- When `\\\"prompt\\\"`:\\n  - Current behavior unchanged (prompt for `source=\\\"message\\\"`, add with comment for editor)\\n- The no-TTY fast path (agent committing) stays unchanged — always adds trailer regardless of setting\\n\\n### Step 4: Remove `Strategy` interface\\n\\n**Files:**\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/strategy.go` — remove `Strategy` interface definition\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit.go` — change `NewManualCommitStrategy()` return type from `Strategy` to `*ManualCommitStrategy`, remove compile-time interface check\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/config.go` — change `GetStrategy()` return type from `strategy.Strategy` to `*strategy.ManualCommitStrategy`\\n\\n**Changes:**\\n- Delete the `Strategy` interface (~140 lines of interface definition)\\n- Keep all method implementations on `ManualCommitStrategy` unchanged\\n- Remove `Name()` and `Description()` methods from `ManualCommitStrategy` (no longer needed for polymorphism)\\n- Keep `StrategyNameManualCommit` constant in `common.go` (still used in commit trailers/metadata)\\n\\n### Step 5: Update all call sites\\n\\n**Files that call `GetStrategy()`** (all in `cmd/entire/cli/`):\\n- `hook_registry.go:113` — uses `.Name()` for logging → replace with `StrategyNameManualCommit` constant\\n- `hooks_git_cmd.go:38` — stores `strategy.Strategy` in struct → change type to `*strategy.ManualCommitStrategy`\\n- `lifecycle.go` (lines 80, 136, 343, 567, 673) — calls methods on strategy → no signature changes needed\\n- `hooks_claudecode_posttodo.go:85` — calls `SaveTaskStep` → no change needed\\n- `re